Title: Student Task Management System using Python (CLI & GUI)
________________________________________
1. Introduction
This project is a task management system designed for students to manage daily activities such as assignments, lectures, and projects. It is implemented in both CLI and GUI using Python.
________________________________________
2. Objectives
•	To manage tasks efficiently 
•	To use list and dictionary as data structures 
•	To develop both CLI and GUI applications 
________________________________________
3. Technologies Used
•	Python 
•	CLI 
•	Tkinter 
________________________________________
4. Features
•	Add task 
•	View tasks 
•	Remove task 
•	Mark task as done 
•	Search task 
•	GUI interface for better usability 
________________________________________
5. Data Structure Used
•	List → stores all tasks 
•	Dictionary → represents each task 
o	id 
o	title 
o	status 
________________________________________
6. Methodology (IPO Model)
Input:
•	User enters task details 
Process:
•	Task stored in list 
•	Updated based on user actions 
Output:
•	Displays task list with status 
________________________________________
7. GUI Description
•	Input field for adding tasks 
•	Buttons for actions (Add, Delete, Done) 
•	Listbox to display tasks 
________________________________________
8. Code Explanation
•	Functions used for modular design 
•	Loop used for continuous operation 
•	Tkinter used for GUI components 
__________
10. Conclusion
This project demonstrates both backend logic and frontend interface development in Python.

